<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="combine-v">combine <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /kəm'baɪn/    美 /kəm'baɪn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(使) 结合；(使) 组合：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Theory must be <strong>combined with</strong> practice. 
理论必须同实践相结合。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The idea of garden city was to <strong>combine</strong> the best of town <strong>and</strong> country in a new kind of settlement.
花园城市的概念就是在一种新的居住形式中把城市和乡村的优点结合起来。</p><footer>2011 江西改</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(使) 化合；(使) 混合：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Steel is produced by <strong>combining</strong> iron <strong>with</strong> carbon.
钢是把铁加碳混合炼制而成的。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>兼备；兼顾：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The hotel <strong>combines</strong> comfort <strong>and</strong> convenience.
这家宾馆既舒适又方便。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Like her mother Marie Curie, Irene <strong>combined</strong> family <strong>and</strong> career.
像她的母亲居里夫人一样，艾琳也兼顾了家庭与事业。</p><footer>2011 陕西改</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>combination /ˌkɒmbɪ'neɪʃn/ n [C]   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>In recent years an English word “infosphere” has appeared, <strong><em>_</em></strong> (combine) the sense of “information” and “atmosphere”.   （2015 福建改）  </li>
<li>— In this day and age, women can have children and jobs as well.
— I can’t agree more. It’s great to have the two <strong><em>_</em></strong>_(combine).  （2010 福建改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. combining  2. combined  </p></div>